ommunication system that has long influenced European culture.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aArt and rhetoriczGreecexHistoryyTo 1500. 0aArt and societyzGreecexHistoryyTo 1500. 0aCommunication and culturezGreecexHistoryyTo 1500. 4aAltgriechisch. 4aAntike. 4aGriechenland. 4aKultur. 4aMündlichkeit. 4aTranskodierung. 4aTransliterationswissenschaft. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Ancient & Classical.2bisacsh  aTranscodification.  aTranslation Studies.  aancient Greece.  aculture.  aorality.1 aAlbano Leoni, Federico, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBonsignori, Chiara, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCapirci, Olga, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDe Sanctis, Dino, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDel Corso, Lucio, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aErcolani, Andrea, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aErcolani, Andrea, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGiordano, Manuela, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGozzano, Simone, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLulli, Laura, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLulli, Laura, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aPalmisciano, Riccardo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPecere, Paolo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSbardella, Livio, econtributor.4ctb4https